On Sunday, December 05, 2004, at 11:40AM, Wayne <mga60(-at-)optonline.net> wrote:

>1: What is the recommended redline for bus engine?

The factory limits it to 5400rpm but torque drops off after 4200rpm so 4500rpm would be a good self imposed limit.

>2: What is the recommended highest cruising rpm?

60-65mph for mileage and to keep the head temps down.

>3: Why would a FI bus have a lower cruising speed than a carb bus?

Gearing.

>4: Would a Porsche 944 tach work on a '79 FI bus?

Probably.

